        "action": "Review the UK Parliament-Government petition site.",
        "additional_details": "Rejected petitions get a copy and paste response. The first chance to reject petitions is done with a copy and paste response \"It is unclear what you want the Government or Parliament to do.\" In the unlikely event that it gets past this point, a government response is given at the first milestone and a farcical \"debate\" confirms the \"government line.\" This has to change.",
        "background": "I believe that the Parliament-Government petition site is a farce and the people's voice is not listened to. Petitions unpopular with government do not get the proper attention and are hamstrung from the start.",
